          <note type="abstract" xml:lang="en" corresp="http://syriaca.org/persons http://syriaca.org/johnofephesus http://syriaca.org/johnofephesus/persons">
            <quote source="#bib5111-3">A scion of the family of the emperor Anastasius and grandson of Theodora, John was a honorary consul and belonged to the top echelons of the imperial hierarchy. Joh. Eph., EH 2.11, records that he was a miaphysite and refused to take the Chalcedonian communion. In 4.35 and 6.12, he is named as one of the envoys sent to the Persian border for peace negotiations.</quote>
